import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import Navbar from './Navbar'; const FieldsPage = () => { // State to store the fetched fields data const [fields, setFields] = useState([]); // Fetch fields data from API endpoint when the component mounts useEffect(() => { fetch('https://api.sportmonks.com/v3/football/venues') .then(response => response.json()) .then(data => { // Set the fetched data to the fields state setFields(data); }) .catch(error => { console.error('Error fetching fields:', error); }); }, []); // Empty dependency array ensures the effect runs only once when the component mounts return (

Fields

{/* Render fetched fields dynamically */} {fields.map(field => (

${field.price}

{field.name}

{field.location}

{/* Render additional field features dynamically */}
{field.category}
{field.size}
))}
); }; export default FieldsPage;
